rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0015
rows.name:
Is it just me, or is the Cloud Sea level
higher than it was before?

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0003
rows.name:
Guess it must be what they
call high tide.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0004
rows.name:
The Cloud Sea level changes
because of the Gula Divine Beast
walking through it, right?

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0005
rows.name:
At times, the clouds reach scarcely
up to the Divine Beast's ankles...

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0006
rows.name:
While at other times, like now, the
clouds are around its belly.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0007
rows.name:
With the clouds at this height, I guess
we won't be able to get back to the
place where we made camp.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0008
rows.name:
Indeed... That area will be submerged
beneath the clouds.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0009
rows.name:
But the Divine Beast's always moving,
so I'm sure the clouds will be lower
again sooner or later.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0011
rows.name:
I'd heard about stuff like this, but it's
kind of amazing seeing it first-hand.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0012
rows.name:
You don't get phenomena like
this in Avaritia, or in Liberalitas,
that's for sure.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0013
rows.name: Alst really is a big place.

rows.label: fev02_100_125_msg0014
rows.name:
All right, that's enough gawping.
Let's get going - Trigo is so
close now, I can smell it.
